Etc...
There are other situations also where new routes are created to simulate taking extra steps or forcing encounters but this is the general idea of how additional potential routes are created and selected for processing.
There are also other instruction types ie: lete / random encounters from a formation set like the floating continent, etc...
The idea that the LOWEST COST route is ALWAYS selected next from the priority queue is the core of how it optimizes for calculated cost and iterates through the possible encounter routes.
Taking an item from the queue actually removes it which is why they are added back in by the way.
